The ttfautohint library has been written by Werner Lemberg <wl@gnu.org>.

It is largely based on the FreeType autohinting module, written by David
Turner <david@freetype.org>.


Special thanks to Dave Crossland <dave@understandingfonts.com> for proposing
the original idea, and to Raph Levien <https://raph.levien.com> and the
Google Web Fonts team <https://fonts.google.com> for providing financial
support to initiate the project.

Thanks also to Extensis, FontLab, Google (again) and all the other people
who contributed to the campaign at Pledgie
<https://web.archive.org/web/20160331223853/https://pledgie.com/campaigns/15816>
for continuing the financial support.


The following people have provided help in developing and testing the
library and front-ends:

